## Technology Stack

`Runtime`: Node.js (v20.19.4+)
`Framework`: Express.js (v4.18.2)
`Database`: MongoDB (v7.0+)
`ODM`: Mongoose
`Environment`: dotenv
`CORS`: cors middleware

## Clone the repository (or navigate to server directory):
`cd server`

## Install dependencies:
`npm install`

## Fix Express version (if needed):
`bashnpm uninstall express`
`npm install express@^4.18.2`

## Environment Configuration:
Create a .env file in the server directory:
PORT=3001
MONGO_URI=mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/weatherDB

## Start MongoDB (if not already running):
`bashbrew services start mongodb-community`

## Start the server:

`node server.js`


